The paper deals with feature extraction for character recognition, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of shape-based graphs and invariant feature sets suggests a machine learning approach, which is also relevant to areas such as machine learning (cs.LG), natural language processing (cs.CL), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
